Privacy Policy

LinkFlow – Chrome Extension
Last Updated: March 3, 2026

⸻

1. Overview

LinkFlow is a Chrome extension that allows users to paste a URL and extract links or structured data from that webpage.

We respect your privacy. LinkFlow does not collect, store, transmit, or sell personal data.

⸻

2. Information We Collect

We do not collect personal information.

Specifically:
	•	We do not collect names, emails, or account information
	•	We do not track browsing history
	•	We do not collect analytics or usage data
	•	We do not use cookies
	•	We do not use third-party tracking tools

When you paste a URL into the extension, the URL is processed locally in your browser solely to extract links or page data.

⸻

3. How LinkFlow Works

When you paste a URL:
	1.	The extension accesses the provided webpage.
	2.	It extracts links or structured data from that page.
	3.	It displays the extracted results inside the extension interface.

All processing occurs locally in the user’s browser environment unless otherwise stated. No extracted content is transmitted to external servers.

⸻

4. Permissions Explanation

The extension may request the following permissions:
	•	activeTab – To access a page when required by user interaction
	•	scripting – To extract links or page data
	•	host permissions – To access the specific URL the user provides
	•	downloads (if applicable) – To export extracted results

Permissions are used strictly to enable the extension’s core functionality.

⸻

5. Data Storage

LinkFlow does not store extracted data on external servers.

If local storage (e.g., chrome.storage) is used, it is limited to saving user preferences (such as settings or formatting choices) and remains stored only within the user’s browser.

⸻

6. Remote Code

This extension does not use remote code.
All functionality is packaged within the extension.

⸻

7. Data Sharing

We do not:
	•	Sell user data
	•	Share user data
	•	Transfer user data to third parties

Because no personal data is collected, no data is shared.

⸻

8. Data Security

All processing occurs locally within the user’s browser. No external databases or servers are used to store extracted information.

⸻

9. Changes to This Policy

If the extension’s functionality changes, this Privacy Policy will be updated and published with a revised effective date.
